description:
&lt;p&gt;Bolton Care Home Liaison team are offering an exciting opportunity for a band 6 CPN to work within the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Care home liaison offers assessment, intervention, practical support and education and early help to residential and nursing homes within the Bolton area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is a real opportunity for someone aiming to make a difference in influencing the care of adults and Older adults within a care home setting in a positive way. The post holder will require experience and knowledge in working with service users with a range of mental health needs and should be able to offer a thorough assessment, treatment and intervention plan focusing on non-pharmacological interventions and a range of psychologically based intervention to care home staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder must be able to demonstrate a range of sound clinical knowledge based and evidence based interventions and be able to work autonomously.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service operates Monday to Friday and the post holder will need access and use of a car in order to perform the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameEmma FaircloughJob titleTeam LeaderEmail addressemma.fairclough@gmmh.nhs.ukTelephone number01204 483771&lt;/p&gt;
